Q1 — Casting and aliasing

Agreed. Removed unnecessary casting as source schema already provides correct data types.
Only retained alias:

transactionType → csv_transactionType

to clearly distinguish CSV fields from MQS fields in the reconciliation output.

Q2 — run_request_date usage

Removed run_request_date parameter to avoid manual intervention.

The script now automatically determines run type:

First run: If target table does not exist or is empty → processes all valid CSV records.
Incremental run: Processes latest available requestDate from source with a small lookback window.

Example:

If latest source date = 2026-04-06 and LOOKBACK_DAYS = 2, the script processes:

2026-04-04 to 2026-04-06

This ensures:

Spillover records are captured
No dependency on manual date inputs

Incremental writes use Delta MERGE, so previously processed records are not deleted.

Q3 — quote_status logic

Current logic:

year(quoteDate) < year(eHubQueuedDatestamp)

This is retained as-is because:

It is used only as an informational flag
It does not affect reconciliation logic or filtering

Acknowledged limitation:

It may flag valid cases (e.g., 2026-12-31 vs 2027-01-01) as invalid

Optional improvement (if needed later):

Can switch to full date comparison using enqueuedTime
Q4 — flow_ naming

Agreed. Renamed flow_ prefix to mqs_ to avoid confusion with interaction flow.

Example:

flow_enqueuedTime → mqs_enqueuedTime

This better reflects the MQS stream source and improves readability across reconciliation outputs.
